success: true
exit_code: 0
----- stdout -----
Bump commands will increment one segment of semver by the specified amount, and print out the mutated version.

Only Major, Minor and Patch are supported. You'll want to consider the `set` subcommand for pre-release and build-metadata.

Usage: sem-tool bump [OPTIONS] <SEMANTIC_VERSION>

Arguments:
  <SEMANTIC_VERSION>
          

Options:
      --bump-major <BUMP_MAJOR>
          

      --bump-minor <BUMP_MINOR>
          

      --bump-patch <BUMP_PATCH>
          

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

